{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:43:05.138Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"7uqqr3oo","input":{"summary":"Successfully implemented the MVP CRUD API routes for ClientAccount under /api/v1/clients.\n\nKey accomplishments:\n1. Created `/api/v1/clients` endpoints in `backend/app/api/routes/clients.py` using modern FastAPI with `Annotated` parameters:\n   - GET /: List all clients with advanced query params for `search` (case-insensitive substring across fields), `status`, `industry`, and `region`.\n   - GET /{client_id}: Retrieve detail of a single client account.\n   - POST /: Create a new client account.\n   - PATCH /{client_id}: Partially update a client account.\n   - DELETE /{client_id}: Support both soft-archiving (default status = 'archived') and physical hard deletion (via `hard_delete=True` parameter) with cascade.\n2. Secured all endpoints with `require_admin` dependency, ensuring strict role-based access control (RBAC) where non-admin users (like client portal users) are blocked with HTTP 403.\n3. Registered the new `/clients` router in `backend/app/api/routes/__init__.py`.\n4. Created an automated DB-connected test suite `backend/app/test_clients_api.py` verifying all CRUD, filtering, validation, soft-archive, and hard-delete operations on SQLite, which passes 100% cleanly.\n5. Ran all backend security/RBAC tests (`test_security_utilities.py`) to confirm everything is cohesive and functional.","verified":true}}}
